<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hal Who?: Actor Hal Linden finds that he is probably eternally typecast as 
"Barney Miller," the laconic New York police captain of the popular 1975-82 TV 
series. At a recent celebrity golf tournament in Vail, Colo., his golf clubs 
seemed to have disappeared in the clubhouse. Linden said they were finally 
found by the manager, who admitted with some embarrassment that they were 
stored under "Miller." "As long as they know me some way, I don't mind," said 
Miller . . . er, ah, Linden. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
