DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HEAD-ON CRASH KILLS 1; 2 OTHERS HOSPITALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ahead-on collision Wednesday morning on a desert stretch of Palmdale Boulevard 
in Palmdale left one man dead and two others critically injured, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The crash occurred shortly after 7:30 a.m. when the driver of a car headed west 
drifted into the oncoming lane and slammed into an eastbound car at about 62nd 
Street East, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department spokesman Ronald 
Thomason. 
</P>
<P>
The first driver died of his injuries about two hours later. His identity was 
withheld until relatives could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
Two other men were hospitalized. Michael Villa Balis, 20, was in critical 
condition at Antelope Valley Medical Center. The other man, whom hospital 
officials declined to identify, was at Palmdale Hospital Medical Center. 
