<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLUMN TO EXPLORE IMPACT OF NEW IDEAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Innovations and the people who create them are interesting, but they become 
compelling when they redefine what we take for granted. This is the first of a 
weekly column that will explore the way new ideas, techniques and technologies 
change both our expectations and our life styles. 
</P>
<P>
Our new columnist, Michael Schrage, writes on topics in which innovation, 
technology and popular culture merge. Previously the technology correspondent 
for the Washington Post, Schrage recently was a visiting scholar at the 
Massachusetts Institute of Technology's Media Lab. 
</P>
<P>
He has been a contributor to the Wall Street Journal, Fortune magazine, Harvard 
Business Review, the Asahi Journal and Rolling Stone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
