<P>
Photo, A Reverent Restoration for Chapel Gary Cooper became an honorary Sioux 
there. Rudy Vallee -- by some accounts -- said his wedding vows there. The 
Ramona Chapel, built about 1925, is perhaps the most popular attraction at 
Newhall's Heritage Square, a collection of antique buildings maintained by the 
Santa Clarita Valley Historical Society, which is restoring the tiny wooden 
building. The society began restoring the outside this summer and poured a 
concrete base for the wooden steps last week. The group hopes to complete the 
work by December, said Bob Diem, who is overseeing the work. Fixing the inside, 
which has suffered from years of neglect, will take longer, he said. "It's a 
delightful little building," said Jerry Reynolds, a society member. "I wish it 
were twice as big as it was. It seats about 12 -- if they're friendly." JOE 
