<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
RETIREES AND COUNCIL MEMBERS TO GOLF FREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Free use of Costa Mesa's golf course was granted to retired city workers and 
former and current City Council members by the council Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Retired employees must have served the city for at least 20 years to be 
eligible for golf passes, which waive green fees at the Costa Mesa Golf and 
Country Club. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Orville Amburgey said the passes were a way to recognize workers 
with long service to the city. 
</P>
<P>
For several years the city has informally allowed former and current City 
Council members to play without charge. Their inclusion in this new policy 
formalizes that practice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
