<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLERGAN LOWERS ITS EARLIER SALES PROJECTION FOR '89 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Citing pressure from competing manufacturers and delay in the release of a new 
product, Allergan Inc. said Wednesday that it is lowering its previously 
announced sales expectations for 1989. 
</P>
<P>
In a prepared statement, the Irvine-based maker of eye-care products said that 
sales were lower than anticipated in its Allergan Optical division due to 
competition and a decline in the market for new contact lenses. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the company said, shipment of a new ophthalmic instrument 
manufactured by its Allergan Humphrey unit has been delayed, based on results 
of recent clinical evaluations and the emergence of new technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
